<HEADLINE>
FT  02 NOV 94 / Zhirinovsky granted US visa
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The US yesterday granted a tourist visa to Mr Vladimir Zhirinovsky, Russia's
nationalist leader, who is scheduled to give an address on the 'New Russia'
next week in San Francisco. 'Our decision to issue Mr Zhirinovsky a visa
neither endorses his views nor supports his ambitions,' a State Department
spokesman said. 'The US government finds his views anathema.' Jewish groups
have condemned the decision.
State Department officials said the visa was for one entry only, whereas
tourist visas are customarily for six months, and the Immigration and
Naturalisation Service may decide to further limit how long Mr Zhirinovsky
stays.
Mr Zhirinovsky applied last month to visit the US for 14 days from this
Friday. He has been invited to speak at the World Affairs Council in San
Francisco next Monday on 'Creating a New Russia'. He is also hoping to visit
Los Angeles, New York and Washington.
</TEXT>
