FT  02 NOV 94 / Peruvian guerrillas surrender
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LIMA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Hundreds of peasants who say they were forced into the service of Peru's
leftist rebels sought last-minute pardons before the deadline for accepting
a government amnesty expired, government officials said yesterday. Elsewhere
scores of repentant Maoist Shining Path guerrillas turned themselves in
before the deadline expired at midnight on Monday.
