<HEADLINE>
FT  02 NOV 94 / World News in Brief: Manager Ardiles sacked by Spurs
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Ossie Ardiles was sacked as manager of Tottenham Hotspur football club by
chairman Alan Sugar, head of the Amstrad computer company. Ardiles, who won
a World Cup winner's medal with Argentina and later played for the north
London club, received a Pounds 500,000 golden handshake. The club is to go
to arbitration this month over its appeal against penalties imposed for
irregular payments to players. It faces the deduction of six Premiership
points, a one-year FA Cup ban and a Pounds 1.5m fine.
FA backs Venables, Page 8;
Observer, Page 21
