<HEADLINE>
FT  01 NOV 94 / Scotland exports reach Pounds 11.5bn
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Manufactured exports from Scotland rose 19 per cent at current prices in the
1993-94 financial year to reach Pounds 11.5bn, accounting for 10.3 per cent
of the UK's manufactured exports.
Exports by Scotland's big electronics sector grew 41.5 per cent while whisky
exports rose 7 per cent.
Growth in sales to North America, the European Free Trade Association and
the Far East far outstripped exports to the European Union, although
Scotland's single biggest export market was France.
The statistics show that Scottish exports have grown faster in the past two
years than in the previous six. The figures are based on a survey carried
out by the Scottish Council Development and Industry.
