 -------------------------------------------------------------------
                              GETTING ABOUT
 -------------------------------------------------------------------
Atlanta's Hartsfield International Airport is the second busiest
airport in the world; the airport claims to have the largest
passenger terminal in the world, handling 50m passengers a year,
with an average of 1,500 flights a day. By air, 80 per cent of the
US population can be reached from Atlanta. Hartsfield airport,
telephone (404) 530-6830, is 13 miles - and 20 minutes' ride - from
central Atlanta by taxi, (except during rush hours). The flat rate
taxi fee to downtown hotels is Dollars 15 for one person, Dollars
16 for two people and Dollars 18 for three.
 -------------------------------------------------------------------
The Atlanta Airport Shuttle (404) 768-7600, costs Dollars 8 one
way to downtown hotels and Dollars 12 one way to suburban areas
such as Lenox Square.
 -------------------------------------------------------------------
The Marta (Metropolitan Atlanta Rapid Transit Authority) rail
system takes 12 minutes and costs Dollars 1.25 one way to downtown
locations.
