<HEADLINE>
FT  01 NOV 94 / London Stock Exchange: Demand for Hanson
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEVE THOMPSON and PETER JOHN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
International conglomerate Hanson was among the most heavily traded stocks
in London as the shares received support from reports of higher commodity
prices.
Analysts said that the price for polyethylene, which is manufactured by
Hanson subsidiary Quantum, had increased by five cents a pound. The
fundamental firmness combined with an increasingly attractive yield has been
encouraging buying interest after a steep slide since the start of the
month. The shares firmed a penny to 231p, with 7.5m traded.
