<HEADLINE>
FT  01 NOV 94 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Landed teas met good general demand, reports the Tea Brokers' Association.
Assams came to a firm market apart from plainest sorts. Brightest Kenya and
Burundi teas sold well at fully firm to dearer rates, particularly pd's.
Below best sorts and coloury mediums were irregular and barely steady.
Ceylons met improved demand with brighter bop's selling well at dearer
rates. Other sorts were irregularly easier. Offshore: good demand with
brighter teas fully firm. Plain Ugandas were unwanted. Quotations: best
available 200p/kg, good 140p/kg, good medium 120p/kg, medium 110p/kg, low
medium 88p/kg. The highest price realised this week was a 205p/kg for an
Assam pf.
