<HEADLINE>
FT  01 NOV 94 / International Company News: Maculan falls 42% in first half
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN RODGER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ZURICH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Operating profit at Maculan, the Austrian construction group with large
operations in eastern Germany, plunged in the first half by 42 per cent to
Sch81.7m (Dollars 7.69m). It also forecast lower net income in the full
year.
Turnover was up 14 per cent to Sch6.9bn, due to a 19 per cent increase in
Germany, which accounted for just over half of group revenue.
The group said the decline in operating profit was due to delays in Russian
housing projects for returning soldiers and to a dispute over the cost of
unforeseen difficulties in a tunnel project in Aus-tria.
</TEXT>
