<HEADLINE>
FT  01 NOV 94 / UK Company News: FT Managed Funds Service
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
From today, the Financial Times will no longer be publishing the
cancellation price on unit trusts - the minimum redemption price. This
follows changes announced by the Securities and Investments Board in
September, designed to liberalise the industry's pricing structure.
Trusts no longer have to publish cancellation prices, though these will
still be available from fund managers, and from today are allowed to impose
exit charges.
In place of the cancellation price, the FT will be publishing notes advising
on exit and other fund charges.
</TEXT>
<XX>
