<HEADLINE>
FT  01 NOV 94 / Observer: Shop early
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mohamed Fayed's war with John Major's government has the oddest
consequences.
Many of Westminster's well-heeled Tory MPs might expect to do some Christmas
shopping at Harrods, the famous Knightsbridge store. Which is of course
owned by Fayed. Hardly the done thing, perhaps, to be spotted crossing
Harrods's threshold at the moment. It might be construed as an act of gross
disloyalty to the prime minister.
